# NSO Assignment 2 – HAProxy + Flask + Ansible

## Description

This project deploys a Flask application on three backend servers (devA, devB, devC) and configures HAProxy as a load balancer.

## Files

* hosts → Ansible inventory
* site.yaml → Playbook
* application2.py → Flask app
* templates/haproxy.cfg.j2 → HAProxy configuration

## Usage

Run:
ansible-playbook -i hosts site.yaml

## Result

HAProxy listens on port 80 and forwards traffic to Flask apps running on port 5000.


